{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Bossard Arena | nickname = | image = Luftbild Bossard Arena 1 Skymotion.ch.jpg | fullname = | location = [[Zug]], [[Switzerland]] | coordinates = {{coord|47|10|37|N|8|30|28|E|region:CH-ZG_type:landmark_source:kolossus-dewiki|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = 2008 | built = | opened = 2010 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = Kunsteisbahn Zug AG | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = Anliker AG and Scheitlin Syfrig Architekten | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[EV Zug]] ([[National League A|NLA]]) | seating_capacity = 7,200 | }}
'''[[Bossard Holding AG|Bossard]] Arena''' is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] located in [[Zug]], [[Switzerland]]. The capacity of the arena is 7,200 spectators and opened in 2010.<ref>http://www.bossard-arena.ch/</ref> It hosts indoor sporting events such as [[ice hockey]]. It hosts the [[EV Zug]] of the [[National League A]]. It replaced [[Eishalle Herti]] as the home of EV Zug.
