{{use dmy dates|date=May 2016}} {{Infobox cricketer | name = Jake Dunford | image = | country = Jersey | fullname = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1994|6|24|df=yes}} | birth_place = | height = | batting = | role = | hidedeliveries = | international = true | date = 22 May 2016 | source = [http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/659087.html ESPNcricinfo] }}
'''Jake Dunford''' (born 24 June 1994) is a [[Jersey cricket team|Jersey]] international cricketer.<ref name="Bio">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/659087.html |title=Jake Dunford |accessdate=22 May 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> He played in the [[2016 ICC World Cricket League Division Five]] tournament.<ref name="DivFive">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/979811.html |title=ICC World Cricket League Division Five, Jersey v Oman at St Saviour, May 21, 2016 |accessdate=22 May 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> Prior to the World Cricket League tournament, he made his [[first-class cricket|first-class]] debut for [[Durham MCC University|Durham MCCU]] against [[Gloucestershire County Cricket Club|Gloucestershire]] on 31 March 2016.<ref name="FC">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/946767.html |title=Marylebone Cricket Club University Matches, Gloucestershire v Durham MCCU at Bristol, Mar 31-Apr 2, 2016 |accessdate=22 May 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref>
He played for Jersey in the [[2016 ICC World Cricket League Division Four]] matches held in Los Angeles.
He is currently the [[ICC World Cricket League]] record holder for the most dismissals in a single tournament, with 21 (18 catches and 3 stumpings) in the ICC WCL Division 5 tournament. This broke the previous record of 19 shared by [[Jeroen Smits]] of the Netherlands (at the 2009 World Cup Qualifier) and [[Denzil Sequeira]] of Botswana (at the 2013 WCL Division Seven).<ref name="record">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/story/1022451.html |title=Jersey captain Gough credits stable squad for promotion |accessdate=3 June 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref>
In April 2018, he was named in Jersey's squad for the [[2018 ICC World Cricket League Division Four]] tournament in Malaysia.<ref name="WCL-Div4">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/cricketinjersey/status/981515595777757184 |title=The 14 man national squad travelling to Malaysia |date=4 April 2018 |accessdate=4 April 2018 |work=Jersey Cricket Board}}</ref><ref name="JerEP">{{cite web|url=https://jerseyeveningpost.com/sport/2018/04/05/chuggys-men-for-mission-to-malaysia/ |title=Chuggy's men for mission to Malaysia |date=5 April 2018 |accessdate=6 April 2018 |work=Jersey Evening Post}}</ref> In August 2018, he was named in Jersey's squad for the [[2018–19 ICC World Twenty20 Europe Qualifier]] tournament in the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/45171461 |title=Jersey name squad for World Twenty20 first-round qualifier |work=BBC Sport |accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/news/808096 |title=Three debutants in Jersey squad for ICC World T20 Europe Qualifier |work=International Cricket Council |accessdate=14 August 2018}}</ref>
