{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = New Strabane Park | nickname = | country = Ireland | image = | location = [[Strabane]], [[Northern Ireland]] | coord = {{coord|54.8333|-7.4664|display=inline}} | establishment = 2008 | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 2017 | club1 = [[North West Warriors]] | date = 15 July | year = 2018 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/6179.html Ground profile }}
'''New Strabane Park''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Strabane]], [[Northern Ireland]].
==History== The ground was established in 2008 as a replacement for the original Strabane Park, which is now the site of an [[ASDA]] superstore. The first major match played on the ground came nine years later in a [[List A cricket|List A]] match between [[North West Warriors]] and [[Northern Knights (cricket team)|Northern Knights]] in the [[2017 Inter-Provincial Cup]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/6179_a.html|title=List A Matches played on New Strabane Park, Strabane|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> with the match ending in no result due to rain. Later that season North West Warriors played a [[Twenty20]] match at the ground against Northern Knights in the [[2017 Inter-Provincial Trophy|Inter-Provincial Trophy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/6179_tt.html|title=Twenty20 Matches played on New Strabane Park, Strabane|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref>
==See also== *[[List of North West Warriors grounds]] *[[List of cricket grounds in Ireland]]
